Figure 2.14  (a) Hypothalamic & pituitary region: sagittal – from right (b) Partial coronal section through A-A.  DN – dorsal nucleus; PN – posterior nucleus; LN – lateral nucleus; TMN – tuberomamillary nucleus; MB – mamillary body; PAR – paraventricular nucleus; DMN – dorsomedial nucleus;
VMN – ventromedial nucleus; PER – periventricular nucleus; Arc – arcuate nucleus; GPL – globus pallidus lateral; GPM – globus pallidus medial; MFB – medial forebrain bundle; ZI – zona incerta.
Source : Fitzgerald (2010).
